column1: What courses are offered at ACEM?
column2: ACEM offers a range of undergraduate and postgraduate programs in engineering and management. The courses include B.Tech in Computer Science & Engineering, Electronics & Communication Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, and Civil Engineering. Additionally, ACEM offers BCA with specializations in General and Data Science, BBA with specializations in General, Finance Services and Banking, and Digital Marketing. The college also provides an MBA program. ACEM is known for its focus on practical learning and live projects, ensuring students are well-prepared for their careers.

To apply for admission at ACEM College, follow these steps:

1. Register yourself at the Institute by calling +91-8527538785.
2. Fill out the Admission Application Form provided by the Institute.
3. Attach necessary testimonials in original and two photocopies, along with six passport size photographs.
4. Submit the application form and documents before August 15th each year.

The Institute will process your application and send it to the University for admission. Ensure you meet the eligibility criteria for your desired course, as the Institute won't be responsible for cancellation of admission or fee refunds in case of non-eligibility.

Admission criteria for LEET students at ACEM College involve the following steps:

1. Register: The student must first register themselves at the Institute by calling +91-8527538785.
2. Application Form: Fill out the Admission Application Form provided by the Institute and attach necessary testimonials in original and two photocopies each along with six passport size photographs.
3. Document Submission: Submit the application form and documents before 15th August every year.
4. Eligibility Check: Carefully check eligibility while taking admission in a particular course. In case of non-eligibility, the institute will not be responsible for the cancellation of admission and fees will not be refunded.
5. Admission Processing: The Institute will process the application and send it to the University for admission.

Please note that LEET students should meet the specific eligibility criteria for their chosen course.

For a student to be eligible for the B.Tech program at ACEM College, they should have completed 10+2 or equivalent examination with Physics, Chemistry, and Mathematics as compulsory subjects. Additionally, they must have secured a valid rank in the Joint Entrance Examination (JEE) Main or any other state-level engineering entrance examination. For BBA programs, students should have passed 10+2 from a recognized board with a minimum of 50% marks in aggregate. There is no specific requirement for LEET students, but they should meet the general eligibility criteria mentioned above.

ACEM offers a variety of engineering, management, and computer application courses. The available branches and courses are:

| Department | Course                                 |
|------------|----------------------------------------|
| Engineering | B.Tech - CSE                          |
|             | B.Tech - CSE - AIML                   |
|             | B.Tech - Mechanical                   |
|             | B.Tech - Civil                        |
|             | B.Tech - ECE                          |
| Management  | BBA                                   |
|             | BBA (FS&B)                            |
|             | BBA-Digital Marketing                |
| Computing   | BCA                                   |
|             | BCA-Data Science                      |
| Postgraduate| MBA                                   |

Please note that the specific course offerings may vary each academic year. For the most up-to-date information, visit the official ACEM website or contact the admission office.

column1: What courses are offered at ACEM?
column2:

| Department | Course |

| Engineering | B.Tech in CSE |
|  | B.Tech in CSE-AIML |
|  | B.Tech in Mechanical |
|  | B.Tech in Civil |
|  | B.Tech in ECE |
| Management | BBA |
|  | BBA (FS&B) |
|  | BBA-Digital Marketing |
| Computer Applications | BCA |
|  | BCA-Data Science |
| Postgraduate | MBA |

For more information about each course, please visit the ACEM website or contact the admission office.

Yes, ACEM College offers various scholarships to support the education of needy and economically weaker students. These scholarships are part of the Chairman's vision, Mr. Dhan Singh Bhadana, to facilitate their participation and development in society. Some notable organizations associated with these scholarships include Hindustan Aeronautics Limited (HAL), Indian Oil Corporation (IOCL), Oil and Natural Gas Corporation Limited (ONGC), Steel Authority of India Limited (SAIL), and Bharat Heavy Electricals Limited (BHEL), among others. Interested students are encouraged to inquire about the specific eligibility criteria and application process during the admission process.

ACEM guarantees 100% placement and provides a minimum of 3 placement opportunities to each eligible student. The college has an outstanding placement record in Delhi/NCR, with many reputed companies visiting the campus for recruitment. The college also collaborates with international universities to offer global exposure to its students.
